# Wireframe Specification

## Required Wireframe Screens

Each group must create the following minimum wireframes and export each screen as PNG.

| Wireframe File | Purpose | Minimum Elements to Show | Related Requirements |
|---|---|---|---|
| /wireframes/homepage.png | Entry point of the Education Campus Hub system | Education Campus Hub title, target users (students, lecturers, academic staff), platform purpose, featured courses/resources/events, main action buttons (Explore Courses, Find Resources, Login/Register), navigation menu | FR-01, FR-02 |
| /wireframes/course-search.png | Search and explore educational resources | Search bar, course/resource cards, subject category, faculty, instructor, availability status, filter options (category, semester, type), View Details button | FR-05, FR-06, FR-08 |
| /wireframes/resource-submission.png | User submission of learning resources | Submission form, resource title, description, category, course name, upload file/link area, required fields, Submit button, Cancel button, validation/error messages, confirmation message | FR-03, FR-10, FR-11 |
| /wireframes/resource-detail.png | Display selected course/resource information | Resource title, description, subject, uploaded by, instructor/owner, date added, resource type, download/view button, rating/feedback area, Back button | FR-07, FR-08 |
| /wireframes/dashboard.png | Student and academic summary view | Total courses, saved resources, completed lessons, recent activities, popular subjects, learning progress, simple charts/cards summary | FR-12 |
| /wireframes/admin-dashboard.png | Admin/lecturer management functions | Resource management table, Add Resource, Edit Resource, Delete Resource, Approve/Reject Submission, Update Status, Manage Users, Search and Filter controls | FR-09, FR-08 |

## Wireframe Quality Rules

- Use consistent navigation, colors, typography, and labels across all screens.
- Avoid decorative-only screens with no educational functionality.
- Show realistic sample course and resource data instead of empty placeholders.
- Every screen must connect directly to the final Education Campus Hub prototype requirements.
- Include interactive elements such as search, filtering, submission, approval, editing, and confirmation messages.
- Wireframes may be created using Figma, Canva, PowerPoint, HTML/CSS, or another suitable prototyping tool.
- Ensure the design is responsive for both desktop and mobile devices.
